The paper deals with wireless communication systems and their security aspects, which are typically studied in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The presence of an eavesdropper and the need for secrecy also suggest the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category. The use of radio-frequency energy and interference, as well as the self-interference issue, may also relate to the Multimedia (cs.MM) and Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories.
